VSwarajhari's monthly programme was a fine vocal concert by Bandlamudi Vasanta Subbalakshmi of Hyderabad, a disciple of Mahamahopadhyaya Dr. Nookala Chinna Satyanarayana and veteran performer and guru Vaijers Balasubramanyam.Subbalakshmi, who is visually-challenged, is doing her post graduation in music from Potti Sriramulu Telugu University. She has also bagged the prestigious Pratibha award from the state government, and is a recipient of Dhirubhai Ambani in Mumbai.Pleasant alapanaEndowed with a bright and clear voice, Subbalakshmi began her concert with Darbar varnnam and followed with Vallabhanayakasya in Begada, concluding it with sparkling kalpana swaras.After singing Syamasastri's Parvati ninu in the rare raga Kalgada, Subbalakshmi rendered as the sub main Karunanidhi of Syamasastri with pleasing alapana and crisp swaras.Her elaboration of Poorvikalyani preceding the kriti Meenakshi of Dikshitar showed good musical depth and the kriti was complemented with exquisite swaras. Sumptuous Todi was presented before Subbalakshmi sang Karunanidhi. Her niraval and kalpanaswaras in Todi were also pleasingly rendered.Oruganti Rajasekhar of Hyderabad provided fine support on violin and senior mridangist Kapa Srinivasa Rao also from Hyderabad gave faithful support. His tani was particularly impressive.The concert came to a close with a thillana in Revathi and a Purandaradas keertana Tamburi Meetedava in Sindbhairavi.
